                                                         PACKAGE MANAGEMENT
=======================================================================================================================================
📦 1. DPKG (Debian Package Manager)
`dpkg` is the **low-level package manager** that directly handles `.deb` package files.

## Check Installed Packages
**Command:**
dpkg -l
```

## Install a Local Package
**Command:**
sudo dpkg -i package.deb
```

## Remove a Package
**Command:**
sudo dpkg -r package_name
```

## Remove Package Including Configuration Files
**Command:**
sudo dpkg -P package_name
```

## Package Information
**Command:**
dpkg -s package_name
```

## List Files Installed by a Package
**Command:**
dpkg -L package_name
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 🚀 2. APT (Advanced Package Tool)

APT works on top of DPKG and automatically resolves dependencies.

## Update Package Database
**Command:**
sudo apt update
```

This downloads the latest package information from repositories.

## Upgrad Installed Packages
**Command:**
sudo apt upgrade
```

Upgrade all installed packages.

## Full System Upgrade
**Command:**
sudo apt full-upgrade
```

Allows installation/removal of packages if required for upgrades.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 📥 Installing Packages

## Install a Package
**Command:**
sudo apt install package_name
```

## Install Multiple Packages
**Command:**
sudo apt install package1 package2 package3
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 🔍 Searching Packages

## Search Available Packages
**Command:**
apt search package_name
```

## Display Package Information
**Command:**
apt show package_name
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 🗑️ Removing Packages

## Remove Package
**Command:**
sudo apt remove package_name
```

## Remove Package and Configuration Files
**Command:**
sudo apt purge package_name
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 🧹 Cleaning Package Cache

APT stores downloaded packages in:
/var/cache/apt/archives/
```

## Clean Cache
**Command:**
sudo apt clean
```

## Remove Unnecessary Packages
**Command:*
sudo apt autoremove
```

**Command (including configuration files):*
sudo apt autoremove --purge
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 📂 Repository Management

Repositories are defined in:
/etc/apt/sources.list
```

## View Repositories
**Command:**
cat /etc/apt/sources.list
```

Official Kali repository:
deb http://http.kali.org/kali kali-rolling main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
```

After modifying repositories:
**Command:**
sudo apt update
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 🔧 Fix Broken Packages

## Configure Unconfigured Packages
**Command:**
sudo dpkg --configure -a
```

## Fix Broken Dependencies
**Command:**
sudo apt --fix-broken install
```

## Repair Package Database
**Command:**
sudo apt update --fix-missing
```
